```python

    if input3 == "nan":
        return "nan"
    
    output = []
    for char in input3:
        if char in input1:
            index = input1.index(char)
            output.append(input2[index] if index < len(input2) else char)
        elif char in input2:
            index = input2.index(char)
            output.append(input1[index] if index < len(input1) else char)
        else:
            output.append(input2[0] if len(input2) > 0 else char)
    return ''.join(output)
```
